commentary: Phehlukwayo to Fakhar Zaman, OUT short ball on middle, top-edged and taken at deep fine leg! Tahir takes a catch near the boundary rope as Fakhar mistimes a pull, but he stumbles backwards slightly while completing the catch, and the umpires want to see if his back leg has touched the rope. It's mighty close.. i'll tell you that. Nifty footwork from Tahir to recover after losing his balance.. but he's managed to keep his heel inside the ropes. Any ballet dancer would be proud of that effort, Fakhar falls for 70

commentary: Imran Tahir to Mohammad Rizwan, no run full on middle stump, and he takes a big stride forward to defend. This is another slider and Rizwan has missed the shot. Ball goes past his inside-edge, and hits his front leg. Big appeal for lbw but not given by the umpire. Tahir convinces Du Plessis to review. What does ball tracking say? Pitches in line...check. Impact on leg stump...check... but the ball is going over the stumps! South Africa lose a review

commentary: Pretorius to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT here comes Rizwan: down the track, goes for an almighty heave-ho across the line. He winds up top-edging it to de Kock behind the stumps. Seeing Rizwan venture down the track, Pretorious digs it short and wide outside off. He asks the batsman to reach out for the ball and hit it. Rizwan can't get enough bat onto it and nicks off. He simply couldn't get going today. He falls for a painstaking 10 off 30 balls

commentary: Usman Shinwari to de Kock, 1 no ball sliced and taken at cover! Back of a length outside off, and de Kock tries to pull this from outside off stump. Extra bounce forces him to fluff the shot, and the lobbed shot goes to Hafeez. Pakistan celebrate but the umpire wants QdK to wait. They want to check for the front-foot no-ball... and Usman has overstepped! And now it's neither a wicket nor a dot ball. One extra run for the no-ball, and now we have a free-hit. How much will this hurt Pakistan?
